"{\"uid\": \"wired.com-story-paris-los-angeles-olympics-hostile-architecture-homeless\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"On a graffiti-stainedsidewalkin Paris, a strange sight appeared days before theOlympic opening ceremonyin July: Around 40 giant cement Lego-like blocks in neat rows beneath the Pont de Stains, a bridge in the northern suburb of Aubervilliers that connects two Olympic sites, the Stade de France and the Parc des Nations.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32, \"end\": 37, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9207584906651021e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 185, \"end\": 191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stains,_Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 0.9854760367634718, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stains\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stains,_Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stains,_Seine-Saint-Denis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strange sight\", \"from\": 39, \"to\": 54}, {\"ngram\": \"neat rows\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"a bridge\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 201}, {\"ngram\": \"the northern suburb\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 224}, {\"ngram\": \"Aubervilliers\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"two Olympic sites\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 273}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parc des Nations\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This place used to be a homeless encampment, where around 100 people, many of them migrants, lived in tents.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This place\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 332}, {\"ngram\": \"a homeless encampment\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 365}, {\"ngram\": \"migrants\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"tents\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thenon July 17, the police arrived andinstructed everyone to leave, as part of a cleanup operation in which authorities put homeless people, members of the Roma community, migrants, and sex workerson busesto other cities, such as Bordeaux or Toulouse.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.984411520135155e-14, \"text\": \"Roma\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\"}, {\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"score\": 0.9999999998462954, \"rank\": 1.2153367652748033e-10, \"text\": \"Bordeaux\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the police\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 457}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 488}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 506}, {\"ngram\": \"a cleanup operation\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 529}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"homeless people\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"migrants\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"sex workerson\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"other cities\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 651}, {\"ngram\": \"Toulouse\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the authorities emptied the area, according to activists, the immovable blocks of concrete were installed in place of the tents, ending any notion the former residents may one day be able to return.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the authorities\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 704}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"activists\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"the immovable blocks\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"concrete\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 779}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"the tents\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 816}, {\"ngram\": \"any notion\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"the former residents\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 856}, {\"ngram\": \"one day\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Campaigners say these bricks are an example of hostile architecture, a term used to describe some of the most visible changes cities and companies make to deter homeless people loitering or sleeping on their properties.\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 1108, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Campaigners\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"these bricks\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 917}, {\"ngram\": \"an example\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 932}, {\"ngram\": \"hostile architecture\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"a term\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 964}, {\"ngram\": \"the most visible changes cities\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"companies\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1035}, {\"ngram\": \"homeless people\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"their properties\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is not new, but it has been intensified in a very specific way during the Olympics,\\\" says Antoine de Clerck, part of Le Revers de la M\\u00e9daille, a group of activists raising awareness of how marginalized people are treated during the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clerck\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\"}, {\"begin\": 1235, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"score\": 0.9999999998440217, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Revers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a very specific way\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1197}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"activists\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"awareness\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1296}, {\"ngram\": \"how marginalized people\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We do not advocate for encampments and squats and shantytowns,\\\" adds de Clerck.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"encampments\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"squats\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"shantytowns\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1425}, {\"ngram\": \"de\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"Clerck\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But to eradicate them, you have to find alternative long-term solutions.\\\"\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"alternative long-term solutions\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite other examples of hostile architecture in Paris, includingpicnic tablesinstalled where people used to sleep, it is the giant Lego-style blocks that have proved most controversial.\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9207584906651021e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other examples\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"hostile architecture\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1621}, {\"ngram\": \"the giant Lego-style blocks\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1670}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have not seen anything quite like this,\\\" says Jules Boykoff, a professor and former professional soccer player who studies the impact of the Olympics on marginalized communities.\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1757, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jules Boykoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"a professor\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"former professional soccer player\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"the impact\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1844}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"marginalized communities\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Typically, hostile architecture is more subtle,\\\" he says, \\\"like a curved bus bench that makes it less comfortable for somebody to sleep.\\\"\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hostile architecture\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1922}, {\"ngram\": \"a curved bus bench\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1973}, {\"ngram\": \"somebody\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2017}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boykoff says the Lego-like blocks are part of a wider trend he has witnessed in other Olympic host cities, such as London in 2012 and Rio de Janeiro in 2016.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2187, \"entities\": [{\"begin