 {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The subredditr/HostileArchitecturehas 147,000 often outraged members.\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3643, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The subredditr\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3588}, {\"ngram\": \"/HostileArchitecturehas\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3611}, {\"ngram\": \"147,000 often outraged members\", \"from\": 3612, \"to\": 3642}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you want to end homelessness, you really have to invest in policies that put people into accommodation, not just displace them from certain places,\\\" says Mar\\u00eda Jos\\u00e9 Aldanas, policy officer at FEANTSA.\", \"from\": 3645, \"to\": 3849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3803, \"end\": 3813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mar\\u00eda_Jos\\u00e9_(singer)\", \"score\": 0.981359767257289, \"rank\": 0.012296881862099445, \"text\": \"Mar\\u00eda Jos\\u00e9\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mar\\u00eda_Jos\\u00e9_(singer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mar\\u00eda_Jos\\u00e9_(singer)\"}, {\"begin\": 3841, \"end\": 3848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FEANTSA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FEANTSA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FEANTSA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FEANTSA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"homelessness\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3677}, {\"ngram\": \"policies\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3716}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3732}, {\"ngram\": \"accommodation\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3751}, {\"ngram\": \"certain places\", \"from\": 3781, \"to\": 3795}, {\"ngram\": \"policy officer\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the US, hostile architecture has taken an even more dystopian turn.\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3858, \"end\": 3860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_